<sect1 id="ladspa-sdk" xreflabel="LADSPA-SDK-&ladspa-sdk-version;">
  <?dbhtml filename="ladspa-sdk.html"?>

  <title>LADSPA-SDK-&ladspa-sdk-version;</title>

  <indexterm zone="ladspa-sdk">
    <primary sortas="a-ladspa-sdk">LADSPA-SDK</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to LADSPA-SDK</title>

    <para>
      The Linux Audio Developer's Simple Plugin API (LADSPA) standard is used
      for piping multiple effects and audio processors into various tools and
      libraries. The LADSPA SDK contains several plugins and the interface
      header file which can be used by several packages. <ulink
      url="&blfs-svn;/multimedia/ffmpeg.html">FFmpeg</ulink> and <ulink
      url="&blfs-svn;/multimedia/mlt.html">MLT</ulink> are notable examples.
      To have support in those packages, you must install this package first
      to not only provide the API, but the plugins as well.
    </para>

    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&ladspa-sdk-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <note><para>
      The site that hosts the download has been known to go offline. In such a
      case, go to the <ulink
      url="https://web.archive.org/">WayBack Machine</ulink> and paste the
      download link into the bar. From there, find a snapshot and it should
      give a suitable link to download from.
    </para></note>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Additional Downloads</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Required patch:
          <ulink url="&dl-root;/ladspa/ladspa_sdk_&ladspa-sdk-version;-arch-1.patch"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">LADSPA-SDK Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Recommended</bridgehead>
    <para role="recommended">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/multimedia/libsndfile.html">libsndfile</ulink>
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of LADSPA-SDK</title>

    <para>
      Apply a patch that fixes a memory leak, a linkage error, and Makefile
      flags:
    </para>

<screen
  remap="pre"><userinput>patch -Np1 -i ../ladspa_sdk_&ladspa-sdk-version;-arch-1.patch</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install LADSPA-SDK by running the following
      commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make -C src targets</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make -C src install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="content">
    <title>Contents</title>

    <segmentedlist>
      <segtitle>Installed Programs</segtitle>
      <segtitle>Installed Plugins</segtitle>
      <segtitle>Installed Directories</segtitle>

      <seglistitem>
        <seg>
          analyseplugin,
          applyplugin, and
          listplugins
        </seg>
        <seg>
          amp,
          delay,
          filter,
          noise, and
          sine (in /usr/lib/ladspa)
        </seg>
        <seg>
          /usr/lib/ladspa
        </seg>
      </seglistitem>
    </segmentedlist>

    <variablelist>
      <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Short Descriptions</bridgehead>
      <?dbfo list-presentation="list"?>
      <?dbhtml list-presentation="table"?>

       <varlistentry id="analyseplugin">
        <term><command>analyseplugin</command></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            analyzes a given LADSPA plugin
          </para>
          <indexterm zone="ladspa-sdk analyseplugin">
            <primary sortas="b-analyseplugin">analyseplugin</primary>
          </indexterm>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="applyplugin">
        <term><command>applyplugin</command></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            passes over an audio file with a given plugin and outputs the new
            audio file
          </para>
          <indexterm zone="ladspa-sdk applyplugin">
            <primary sortas="b-applyplugin">applyplugin</primary>
          </indexterm>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="listplugins">
        <term><command>listplugins</command></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            gives a list of available LADSPA plugins
          </para>
          <indexterm zone="ladspa-sdk listplugins">
            <primary sortas="b-listplugins">listplugins</primary>
          </indexterm>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

    </variablelist>

  </sect2>

</sect1>
